Intel=E2=80=99s Plunging Margin
-----------------------

This has resulted in a triple-whammy to Intel=E2=80=99s earnings:

* First, volumes were down dramatically thanks to high inventories amongst =
OEMs (a less charitable interpretation is that Intel stuffed the channel).
* Second, prices are down thanks to Intel needing to increasingly discount =
to counter AMD=E2=80=99s total-cost-of-ownership advantage.
* Third, the largest cost of goods sold for a chip is fixed costs, the depr=
eciation of which is incurred no matter how many chips are sold; that means=
 that fewer chips sold for lower prices has an outsized impact on gross mar=
gins.

